`,"Most games treat save/load as a non-diegetic affordance, giving players total memory control. But narrative games that do touch on this -- such as Undertale or The Forgotten City -- typically comment on save mechanics only as a narrative layer. My approach is different, as I systematize save/load as part of the players action space."]}),`
