`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:"For players, the effect is subtle but meaningful. Saving stops being a utility function and becomes a choice the world can react to. Instead of the world resetting politely around you, the game begins to acknowledge your habits. If you always reload before a bad outcome, the world starts to treat that pattern as part of who you are."}),`
